data.story: Joanna Kozieńska updated the description of the group West Coast Swing Dance Chart.
data.message:
Welcome on board of our WCS Dance Chart! Share your favourite WCS music with our international (although still mostly Polish ;)) community!

Couple of rules to follow, so as to make our quest here smooth and painless:

We've tried out a number of ideas with regards to posting new songs, and THE QUEUE seems to be the only one that prevents us all from being buried daily under the neverending avalanche of WCS pieces. 

How does it work?

- we only publish 2 songs per day, Mon.till Fri.

- each Friday you get a recap of what has been published during the week, so that you can easily keep track of the new songs,

- we don't publish on weekends, so that there's time to actually listen to every new song and decide if it deserves a thumbs up or not,

- the number of people who want to share their songs is usually higher than the number of free slots we can provide each week (2 songs per day = 10 slots in total per week), so, please, don't get worried or frustrated if your piece doesn't get published immediately: it's sitting safe and sound in the queue and the world is definitely going to see it when the right time comes :) 

BEFORE YOU POST anything: please, please use the search bar on top of the page and make sure that you're the first one who thought about sharing that particular song, so that we can avoid publishing the same piece twice :)

Communication:
the Chart was created by a group of Polish Westies, so don't be surprised if you see comments/posts written in our mother tongue :)

We all know English fairly well and we promise  we'll try to use it more often, so that our English-speaking members can feel more at home here :) Don't hesitate to post/comment/ask questions/share your thoughts in English - everybody will understand :)

Now go ahead, browse away through our archives and post the songs you would like us to triple step to! :)

data.name: Photos from Joanna Kozieńska's post
data.message:
[WCS Weekly Westletter]

Hello, Sweeties! :)

Kolejny piąteczek na Charcie!
Zanim przejdę do podsumowania - jest sprawa. A nawet kilka :)

- first of all, as more and more English-speaking Westies are joining the group, let me say a quick hello to our most recent members :) Cynthia, Ashley, Jennifer, Barb, Arthur, Elisabeth, Lu, Bernd, Stellan, Carlo: welcome! We're glad you've decided to join us in our pursuit of good WCS music to dance and practice to,  and we'd appreciate any contribution on your part. 
Although most people here tend to write their comments in Polish (old habits die hard ;)), we're all perfectly capable of using English, so if you have any questions/comments/thoughts, go ahead and share them, we'll understand :)
 
Also, each Friday I prepare a short recap of what has been posted in the group during the week and I always do that in Polish. 
I have no idea how the FB translator deals with a longer text, so if, once translated, my Friday posts seem like utter nonsense, please let me know and I'll prepare a proper English version for you :)

Dołączam również cieplutkie cześć dla wszystkich Polaków, którzy do nas ostatnio dołączyli :) Fajnie, że jesteście!

- a oto i link do naszej cudownej playlisty 15+:
https://open.spotify.com/user/jesiennik/playlist/0IHRdITZ6ZbRWJemCU8eM0

 Już jest publiczna i będzie na bieżąco uzupełniana o nowe hiciory.

Brakuje na niej dosłownie kilku kawałków, których absolutnie nie można znaleźć na Spotify, ale cała reszta się zgadza.

- przy okazji przygotowań do imprezy wyszło też w praniu, że brakuje na Charcie westowych pewniaków - albo się zgubiły albo zniknęły, albo zapomnieliśmy dodać, bo przecież oczywiste, że się do tego tańczy. Postanowiłam w związku z tym, na ile będę w stanie, uzupełnić Chart w weekend, kontynuując akcję

[Wielkie Ogarnianie Charta: piosenki zaginione w akcji]

PROŚBA: jeśli ktoś po uważnym przeszukaniu Charta zauważy brak oczywistego hiciora, wrzucajcie do kolejki z opisem takim, jak w nawiasie powyżej, będziemy to klepać na bieżąco, żeby był porządek w grupie :) 

No, to do podsumowania!
Coś mi się pochrzaniło z przedimprezowych emocji i ogólnego chaosu, jaki zapanował na Charcie, no i zaklepałam 12 zamiast 10 piosenek, uprasza się o wybaczenie :D
